{# Short front-matter for weak models: hard sequencing + eval gate. Included by plan/build/ship skills. #}

## Continuity & quality gates (read first)

**Standard pipeline:** `/harness-plan` → `/harness-build` → `/harness-ship`.  
`/harness-ship` does **not** write feature code — it runs tests, **mandatory 5-role code eval**, `harness save-eval`, `harness gate`, then push/PR.

**Do not end the session until:**
- After **plan + review gate:** you have started **`/harness-build`** in the **same** conversation (do not stop at `plan.md` only).
- After **build (implementation committed):** you have started **`/harness-ship`** in the **same** conversation (do not stop at “tests pass” only).
- During **`/harness-ship`:** you have run **eval** (5 roles + `harness save-eval`) and **`harness gate`** — **never** skip eval because “pytest is green”.

**Mechanical check (optional):** run `harness workflow next` in the repo root for a one-line `HARNESS_NEXT ...` hint tied to `workflow-state.json`.
